<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96711767225819></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96711767225819><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96711767225819>RE: Pet Weapons - what to use and when.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96711767225819#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>390 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 24th 7:47 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.77]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good post Zyphyr!!! Now here is a little secret...on the boat from FP to BB get off at the first stop. This is sister isle. Go inside the little hut that is right there by the dock. Inside you will find RUSTY HALBERDS for sale. Give these to your pet and they will do 20 DAMAGE A HIT. Very nice for your level 4-16 pets. Plus, it only costs 1pp to buy 3 of them. However they are very heavy, and won't fit in any containers except a dimensional pocket. So you will have to put all the extra ones you won't be using in the bank, int heir own slot. This is a VERY good trick though becuase when i made my 2nd magician character about half a year ago, I gave my pet a rusty halberd and could easily break and hold the kobold camp in Steamfont at level 4. <br><br>Okay that was a low level tactic. Now here is a high level one. At level 29 get two gnoll hide lariats. Go to Rathe mountains. Summon an air pet, buff it with burnout 2, and give him the two gnoll hide lariats. Now go solo giant skelatons and cyclops's(how the heck do you say the plural of cyclops??????). Anyway, against the giant skelatons it will be VERY easy...send your pet in and then cast your level 24 Shock spell 3 times. The massive stun proc the air will do with the lariats combined with his own stun will easily keep the skelatons on him no matter what you do. Just make sure you outdamage your pet so you get full EXP. for the kill. If you are gonna solo cyclops's at level 29 you won't want to do a huge burn so quick, becuase the are an avaerage of 5 levels higher than giant skelatons and won't get stunned as much. They will get stunned a fair amount of the time though. Just Blast when needed and Try to outdamage your pet without the cyclops aggroing on you. You can get to level 34 soloing giant skels/cyclop's and then from 34 to 39 just on cyclops's (at level 34 cyclop's become pretty easy and you will be able to kill them quickly).<br><br>Okay there are my low and high level weapon tips.<br><br>Corpusnuntia/Divineshadow/Naltec/Plantmaster/natalos/Zuranthium<br><br>Player of many characters on the Namelee server.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
